        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q5783996"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q629000"/>
        <ontology:isPresentedBefore rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N220_VC_12_SK/event/ev8"/>
        <ontology:is_identified_by rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/appellation/Interest_on_this_VC"/>
        <ontology:partOfNarrative rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N220_VC_12_SK"/>
        <ontology:took_place_at rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/phenomenal_place/49.28468489187888_19.16627629813956"/>
        <ontology:took_place_at rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/place/1"/>
        <ontology:hasDescription>A new trend in wooden buildings like houses, cottages, restaurants, and guesthouses is rising over the last few years. Wood production for houses is connected to forest land use. The enterprises offering wood constructions use e-commerce. This VC focuses on wood house builders who use wood from national forests. Wooden houses were build in the past in Slovak mountains. Nowadays, the wood houses are a novelty on a market and are gaining popularity. It is an additional use of the wood from the Slovak forests.  </ontology:hasDescription>
    </NamedIndividual>
    


